msgid "When a network application does not run as expected, it is important to be able to look under the hood. Even when everything seems to run smoothly, running a network diagnosis can help ensure everything is working as it should. Several diagnosis tools exists for this purpose; each one operates on a different level. It would go beyond the scope of this book to discuss all tools, so we will focus on the more well-known and commonly used tools in the following sections."
